<https://ref.openepcis.io/vocab/batterypass-ready/1.3#CapacityFade>
    a rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:label "Capacity Fade"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "The capacity fade is the Decrease over time and upon usage in the amount of charge that a battery can deliver at the rated voltage, with respect to the original rated capacity (see BattReg Annex IV (2)) as declared by the manufacturer.\n\nDIN DKE Spec 99100 chapter reference: 6.7.2.4"@en ;
    skos:definition "The capacity fade is the Decrease over time and upon usage in the amount of charge that a battery can deliver at the rated voltage, with respect to the original rated capacity (see BattReg Annex IV (2)) as declared by the manufacturer.\n\nDIN DKE Spec 99100 chapter reference: 6.7.2.4"@en ;
    skos:note "GEFEG BatteryPass-Ready longlist v1.3 attribute (group PerformanceAndDurability). Definition sourced from the corresponding BatteryPass Consortium SAMM property (io.BatteryPass.*), which the longlist derives from."@en ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <https://ref.openepcis.io/vocab/batterypass-ready/1.3> ;
    dcterms:source <https://thebatterypass.eu/battery-pass-ready/publications/> .

<https://ref.openepcis.io/vocab/batterypass-ready/1.3#CapacityThresholdForExhaustion>
    a rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:label "Capacity Threshold For Exhaustion"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "The percentage of SOCE, above which the battery is still considered operational as EV battery in its current life, as provided by the economic operator.\n\nDIN DKE Spec 99100 chapter reference: 6.7.6.9"@en ;
    skos:definition "The percentage of SOCE, above which the battery is still considered operational as EV battery in its current life, as provided by the economic operator.\n\nDIN DKE Spec 99100 chapter reference: 6.7.6.9"@en ;
    skos:note "GEFEG BatteryPass-Ready longlist v1.3 attribute (group PerformanceAndDurability). Definition sourced from the corresponding BatteryPass Consortium SAMM property (io.BatteryPass.*), which the longlist derives from."@en ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <https://ref.openepcis.io/vocab/batterypass-ready/1.3> ;
    dcterms:source <https://thebatterypass.eu/battery-pass-ready/publications/> .

<https://ref.openepcis.io/vocab/batterypass-ready/1.3#CapacityThroughput>
    a rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:label "Capacity Throughput"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "The data attribute should be reported as measured for further potential processing. In addition, the normalisation by capacity may add a further useful value that ensures comparability among battery sizes.\n\nDIN DKE Spec 99100 chapter reference: 6.7.6.8"@en ;
    skos:definition "The data attribute should be reported as measured for further potential processing. In addition, the normalisation by capacity may add a further useful value that ensures comparability among battery sizes.\n\nDIN DKE Spec 99100 chapter reference: 6.7.6.8"@en ;
    skos:note "GEFEG BatteryPass-Ready longlist v1.3 attribute (group PerformanceAndDurability). Definition sourced from the corresponding BatteryPass Consortium SAMM property (io.BatteryPass.*), which the longlist derives from."@en ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <https://ref.openepcis.io/vocab/batterypass-ready/1.3> ;
    dcterms:source <https://thebatterypass.eu/battery-pass-ready/publications/> .

